 heroism, sacrifice, and redemption hidden within ordinary American landscapes, underscoring the crucial necessity of defending—and exercising—our right to vote at this tenuous moment for American democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican AmericansxViolence againstzSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th centuryvPictorial works. 0aCivil rights demonstrationszSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th centuryvPictorial works. 0aCivil rights movementszSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th centuryvPictorial works. 0aCivil rights movementszSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aCivil rights workersxViolence againstzSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th centuryvPictorial works. 0aDocumentary photography. 0aPhotography, Artistic. 7aPhotography / General.2bisacsh  aBirmingham Alabama, 16th street Baptist church.  aVoting Rights Act, Voting Rights Act of 1965, voting rights, civil rights movement, American history, photographers, photo essays, Selma, Selma Alabama, Memphis.1 aAbranowicz, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbranowicz, Zander, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHannah-Jones, Nikole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32174440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477329207423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477329207/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles